olive oil
1 carrot
1 bag Silverbeet
1 stalk celery
1 packet chicken breast
1 sachet red lentils
1 packet tomato paste
¾ cup boiling water
1 packet coconut milk
30 g butter
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 sachet Mild North Indian Spice Blend
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Boil
the kettle.
• Thinly slice carrot into rounds. Roughly chop
silverbeet. Finely chop celery. Rinse red lentils.
• Cut chicken breast into 2cm chunks.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over high heat. Cook chicken, carrot and celery,
tossing, until slightly tender and browned,
5-6 minutes.

TIP: The chicken will finish cooking in the oven!

• Add Mumbai spice blend, mild North Indian
spice blend and tomato paste, and cook,
tossing, until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add the boiling water(3/4 cup for 2 people /
1 1/2 cups for 4 people), coconut milk and
lentils. Stir to combine and bring to a simmer,
1-2 minutes.

• Transfer chicken dhal mixture to a baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil and bake until liquid is
absorbed and lentils have softened,
20-25 minutes.

• When the dhal has 10 minutes cook time
remaining, stir silverbeet, the butter and a
pinch of salt through dhal, re-cover, then return
to the oven and continue baking.

TIP: If the lentils are dry, stir through a splash of
water.

• Divide cheat's baked chicken dhal between
bowls.
• Dollop over Greek-style yoghurt to serve. Enjoy!

Little cooks: Kids can add the finishing touch and
dollop over the yoghurt.